\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 50. A. capitata} Kit. ex Schultes,{\i  Österreichs Fl.} ed. 2,{\b  1}: 312 (1814). Like {\b 49} but stems (5-)10-20(-35) cm, shortly hairy only at base; leaves (15-)18-25(-30) × (0·5-)1-1·5 mm, linear-lanceolate, the lowest shortly hairy, the upper glabrous, the margin distinctly revolute; corolla more or less infundibuliform. 2n = 22. {\i Calcareous mountain rocks. • S. & E. Carpathians; C. Bulgaria.} Bu Rm.
