\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 51. A. hexaphylla} All.,{\i  Fl. Pedem. }{\b 1}: 12 (1785). Like {\b 49} but stems glabrous; leaves 14-25 × 1-1·5 mm, linear-lanceolate,glabrous, the margin scabridulous; pedicels 0·5-1·5(-3) mm; corolla-tube 5-6 mm; lobes 2-3 mm, more or less incurved. 2n = 22. {\i Calcareous mountain rocks. • S.W. Alps, northwards to} c. 45°{\i  N}. Ga It.
